// Undo/redo history manager
// Maintains a two-stack (undo/redo) command history with support for atomic batching, and provides a factory for simple SceneNode property-change entries.
// synced: 2026-03-26T00:00:00Z

CLASS UndoManager
  State: undoStack (UndoEntry[]), redoStack (UndoEntry[]), batchEntries (UndoEntry[] | null), batchLabel (string)

  FUNCTION apply(entry: UndoEntry) -> void [2026-03-26]
    Executes entry.forward() immediately, then pushes the entry to the active batch or the undo stack (clearing redo).

  ---

  FUNCTION push(entry: UndoEntry) -> void [2026-03-26]
    Pushes a pre-executed entry to the active batch or the undo stack without calling forward(). Clears redo stack.

  ---

  FUNCTION undo() -> string | null [2026-03-26]
    Pops the top undo entry, calls its inverse(), moves it to the redo stack, and returns its label. Returns null when nothing to undo.

  ---

  FUNCTION redo() -> string | null [2026-03-26]
    Pops the top redo entry, calls its forward(), moves it to the undo stack, and returns its label. Returns null when nothing to redo.

  ---

  FUNCTION beginBatch(label) -> void [2026-03-26]
    Starts accumulating entries into a batch with the given label. Subsequent apply/push calls collect into batchEntries instead of the main stack.

  ---

  FUNCTION commitBatch() -> void [2026-03-26]
    Wraps all accumulated batch entries into a single compound UndoEntry whose forward iterates entries in order and whose inverse iterates in reverse, then pushes to the undo stack.

  ---

  FUNCTION clear() -> void [2026-03-26]
    Empties both stacks and cancels any open batch.

---

FUNCTION createPropertyChange(node, changes, label) -> UndoEntry [2026-03-26]  EXPORT
  Snapshots the node's current values for all keys in changes, then returns an UndoEntry whose forward applies changes and whose inverse restores the snapshot.
